## Data Science In Apache Spark
### EPA Air Now
#### Exploring EPA Air Now Data 

**Language**: Scala
**Requirements**: 
- [HDP 2.6.X]
- Spark 2.x

**Author**: Ian Brooks

**Follow**: [LinkedIn Ian Brooks PhD](https://www.linkedin.com/in/ianrbrooksphd/)

**Source Data**: [EPA Air Now Search Site](https://aqs.epa.gov/api)

**Date Format**: [Oracle Date Format](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/i18n/format/simpleDateFormat.html)

**File Upload:**: Upload the source data json  files to HDFS in the /tmp directory

msg.data:
Data Science In Apache Spark

EPA Air Now

Exploring EPA Air Now Data

Language: Scala
Requirements:

  • [HDP 2.6.X]
  • Spark 2.x

Author: Ian Brooks

Follow: LinkedIn Ian Brooks PhD

Source Data: EPA Air Now Search Site

Date Format: Oracle Date Format

File Upload:: Upload the source data json files to HDFS in the /tmp directory

paragraphs.title: Load Dependency Library
paragraphs.text:
%spark2.dep 

z.load("com.databricks:spark-csv_2.11:1.5.0")

%spark2.dep

z.load("com.cloudera.sparkts:sparkts:jar:0.4.0")

paragraphs.title: Download Data Files and Copy To HDFS
paragraphs.text:
%sh

#Enable SH Zeppelin interpreter

# Download Data from Github
wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BrooksIan/EPAAirNow/master/AQDM_358425767.txt -O /tmp/AQDM_358425767.txt

# Make HDFS Directory and Load CSV files into HDFS
hadoop fs -mkdir /tmp/
hadoop fs -put /tmp/AQDM_358425767.txt /tmp/AQDM_358425767.txt

hadoop fs -ls /tmp/AQDM*

paragraphs.title: Initialize Spark Session
paragraphs.text:
%spark2

import org.apache.spark.sql.SparkSession
val spark: SparkSession = SparkSession.builder
  .appName("EPAAir")  // optional and will be autogenerated if not specified
  .master("local[*]")               // avoid hardcoding the deployment environment
  .enableHiveSupport()              // self-explanatory, isn't it?
  .config("spark.sql.warehouse.dir", "target/spark-warehouse")
  .getOrCreate

spark.version

paragraphs.title: Manage Timestamp
paragraphs.text:
%spark2

import org.apache.spark.sql.functions.{to_date, to_timestamp}

val modifiedDF = df_WholeSetRaw.withColumn("DateSub", expr("substring(datetime, 1, length(datetime)-5)") )


val modifiedDF1 = modifiedDF.withColumn("timestamp", unix_timestamp($"DateSub", "yyyymmdd'T'kkmm").cast(TimestampType))

modifiedDF1.cache()
modifiedDF1.printSchema()
modifiedDF1.take(1)

modifiedDF1.createOrReplaceTempView("EPAAIRNOW")

paragraphs.title: Query Raw Table
paragraphs.text:
%spark2.sql

select * from EPAAIRNOW limit 100

paragraphs.title: Prepare Site Locations Information
paragraphs.text:
%spark2.sql

select distinct site, lat, lon from EPAAIRNOW order by site limit 100
%spark2.sql

paragraphs.title: Build Dataframe for Site Locations and Save to Zeppelin Backend
paragraphs.text:
%spark2

val siteDF = spark.sql("select distinct lat, lon, site from EPAAIRNOW")

siteDF.cache()
siteDF.take(20)
siteDF.count()

z.angularBind("SiteLocations1", siteDF.take(30))

paragraphs.title: Display Locations
Records By Site
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select site, count(site) from EPAAIRNOW group by site

paragraphs.title: Records By Action Code
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select action_code, count(action_code) from EPAAIRNOW group by action_code

paragraphs.title: Records By Method Code
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select method_code, count(method_code) from EPAAIRNOW group by method_code

paragraphs.title: Records By GISDatum
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select GISDatum, count(GISDatum) from EPAAIRNOW group by GISDatum

paragraphs.title: Records By Parameter Code
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select parameter, count(parameter) from EPAAIRNOW group by parameter

paragraphs.title: Records By Ele
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select elev, count(elev) from EPAAIRNOW group by elev

paragraphs.title: AirQuality Value From Sites By Timestamp
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select timestamp, value, site from EPAAIRNOW where value > 0 group by timestamp, value, site  limit 1000

paragraphs.title: AirQuality Value Min, Max, & Avg From All Sites By Date
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select dayofyear(timestamp), avg(value), min(value), max(value) from EPAAIRNOW group by timestamp, value limit 1000

paragraphs.title: Air Quality Value Date: Jan 5 2018 From All Sites
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select timestamp, value, site from EPAAIRNOW where dayofyear(timestamp) = 5 and value > 10 group by timestamp, value, site order by timestamp limit 1000

paragraphs.title: AirQuality Value By Timestamp From Site: 840480290032
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select timestamp, value, site from EPAAIRNOW where site = 840480290032 group by timestamp, value, site order by timestamp limit 1000

paragraphs.title: Interpolation Results - AirQuality Value By Timestamp From Site: 840480290032
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select timestamp, value, site from Interpolation where site = 840480290032 and cast(timestamp as string) like '2018-01-02%' group by timestamp, value, site order by timestamp limit 1000

paragraphs.title: MPC Values (Min, Max, Avg) By Timestamp From All Sites
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select timestamp, site, mpc_value from EPAAIRNOW group by timestamp, mpc_value, site limit 1000

paragraphs.title: MPC Value By Timestamp From Two Sites
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select timestamp,  mpc_value, site from EPAAIRNOW  where site = 840480430101 or site = 840482450102 group by timestamp, mpc_value, site limit 1000
%sql
